#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:115 4ce2987107674e13a757a9e371fd7b9d
msgid "Instructional video series: The project's problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:120 d2c4ad3f5b4c4f26aa8d71db4c9063a4
msgid ""
"There is user demand for high-quality, up-to-date video guides that take "
"users from zero Linux knowledge to using Qubes as a daily driver and "
"performing specific tasks inside of Qubes, but almost no such videos "
"exist. Although most of the required knowledge is documented, many users "
"report that they would prefer to watch videos rather than read text or "
"that they would find videos easier to understand and follow along with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:124 6a208c970aff4a47999cafd4613cd5b7
msgid "Instructional video series: The project's scope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:129 b66323783e314712a4650bf074e8ecfa
msgid ""
"This project consists of creating a series of instructional videos that "
"satisfy the following criteria:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:131 6e0dc23177df48dbb205ee7220b1e131
msgid ""
"Prospective users who are not yet familiar with Linux or Qubes OS can "
"easily understand and follow the videos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:133 8aa52416ef5b49f0b3bff9ce01cdbfe3
msgid ""
"The videos make a good effort to catch and keep the attention of their "
"target audience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:135 1a4a9462fd434528b68d4bde933c9078
msgid ""
"Users can follow the videos step-by-step to install Qubes OS and "
"accomplish various tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:137 a0030c889e474297943a5f800e860c6c
msgid ""
"The videos show the actual software being used (i.e., Qubes OS and any "
"relevant software running inside of it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:139 77cd456a937c42538c646b1378e44632
msgid ""
"The videos are technically accurate, include security warnings where "
"appropriate, and use terminology in a way that is consistent with the "
"rest of the documentation (also see the :doc:`glossary "
"</user/reference/glossary>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:141 d15f3c5a7cbd4fc3b455ba6420aa3a3d
msgid ""
"The video series is comprehensive enough that users do not need to "
"consult the documentation or ask questions (e.g., on the forum) in order "
"to accomplish the most popular tasks and activities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:143 839daee18e4d458db5940e1d97166356
msgid "The videos include voice narration. (Showing the speaker is optional.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:145 58fd45e187c24a9aa189b8381f43ad35
msgid ""
"The quality of the videos is consistent with current standards regarding "
"things like editing, transitions, animations, lighting, and audio "
"quality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:147 63dd102f312043aaaf44efbed9acfa47
msgid "The videos are in high definition (minimum 1080p, preferably 4k)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:149 b3ea755d5b8d41f9b1e7fc172d71d73c
msgid ""
"The videos are separated into a series, where each video is an "
"appropriate length and is appropriately connected to the other videos in "
"the series."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:151 10366bb9c9be458496d0fa001363c3c3
msgid ""
"The videos are suitable for upload and sharing on popular video-sharing "
"and social-media platforms, such as YouTube and Twitter. (The account or "
"channel under which the videos are uploaded is open to discussion on "
"platforms where the Qubes OS Project does not already have a significant "
"established presence, such as YouTube.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:153 12fbd67d659e49ffaffb10a2566c1832
msgid ""
"The videos are suitable for embedding in appropriate places in the Qubes "
"documentation. (E.g., a video on how to update Qubes OS should be "
"appropriate for appearing on the :doc:`how to update </user/how-to-guides"
"/how-to-update>` page.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/gsod.rst:155 f8e35a582e534d0599a23d3156e136dc
msgid ""
"Where possible, the videos should strive to be version-independent. (For "
"example, a video explaining the template system should still be relevant "
"many releases from now if the template system has not changed.)"
msgstr ""

